<subSubSection pageId="286" pageNumber="287" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="286.[151,1437,260,360]" pageId="286" pageNumber="287">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,260,287]" pageId="286" pageNumber="287">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Macropterous 
<specimenCount box="[443,464,262,288]" pageId="286" pageNumber="287" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1893" box="[501,596,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Bocchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="286" pageNumber="287" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[501,596,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="286" pageNumber="287">Bocchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with head mostly yellow-testaceous and completely granulate (
<figureCitation box="[1307,1424,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURE 112" captionStartId="287.[151,250,1566,1591]" captionTargetBox="[156,1426,446,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@287.[151,1436,445,1553]" captionTargetPageId="287" captionText="FIGURE 112. Habitus of Bocchus species holotypes.A: B. martellii Olmi. B: B. niger Olmi. C: B. nigroflavus Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov.; head vertex and mesoscutum sculpture. D: B. parkeri Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov.; head vertex and mesoscutum sculpture. Scale bar: A: 2.31 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3336898/files/figure.png" pageId="286" pageNumber="287">Fig. 112C</figureCitation>
); OPL about twice as long as OOL; mesoscutum granulate; forewing hyaline, without dark transverse bands or spots; enlarged claw with long row of teeth (
<figureCitation box="[578,696,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 110" captionStartId="284.[151,250,1511,1536]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,197,1493]" captionTargetId="figure@284.[151,1436,193,1499]" captionTargetPageId="284" captionText="FIGURE 110. Chelae of Bocchus species holotypes. A: B. krombeini Olmi. B: B. martellii Olmi. C: B. niger Olmi. D: B. nigroflavus Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov. E: B. piceus Olmi. F: B. rassitus Olmi &amp; van Harten. Scale bar: A, D, F: 0.06 mm; B: 0.08 mm; C: 0.09 mm; E: 0.12 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3336894/files/figure.png" pageId="286" pageNumber="287">Fig. 110D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
